# Sanad Backend - Project Rules

## Stack & Overview
- **Framework**: NestJS 11
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Prisma 5
- **Validation**: class-validator, class-transformer
- **Docs**: Swagger at `/api`
- **Auth**: JWT via @nestjs/jwt

## Architecture
Use the **Controller → Service → Repository** pattern:

- **Controller**: HTTP handling, DTOs, Swagger decorators
- **Service**: Business logic, orchestration
- **Repository**: Data access only (extend `BaseRepository`, inject `PrismaService`)

## Module Structure
Each feature module lives under `src/<module>/`:
- `*.controller.ts` – routes
- `*.service.ts` – business logic
- `*.repository.ts` – Prisma queries
- `dto/*.dto.ts` – DTOs with validation
- `validators/` – custom validators when needed

## DTOs & Validation
- Use `class-validator` decorators on all DTOs
- For “exactly one of A or B” (e.g. email XOR mobile), use `@ValidateIf((o) => !o.mobile)` and `@ValidateIf((o) => !o.email)` with `@IsNotEmpty`
- Add `@ApiProperty` / `@ApiPropertyOptional` on DTO fields for Swagger
- Prefer shared validators in `src/shared/validators/` (e.g. `ExistingEntityRecordValidator` with `inverse` for uniqueness)

## Swagger
- Add `@ApiTags` on controllers
- Use `@ApiOperation` and `@ApiResponse` on endpoints
- Document DTOs with `@ApiProperty` (examples, descriptions)

## Shared Code
- `src/shared/validators/existing-entity-record.validator.ts` – reusable “exists” / “unique” validator
- `src/shared/generics/repository.abstract.ts` – base for repositories
- Extend `BaseRepository` and implement `IEntityExistsRepository` when using `ExistingEntityRecordValidator`

## E2E Tests
- Use `testRequest` from `test/config/request.ts` with `HTTP_METHODS_ENUM`
- `global.app` and `global.prisma` are set in `test/config/setup-e2e.ts`
- Clear DB in `beforeEach` for isolation
- Register setup/teardown in `test/config/jest-e2e-setup.ts`

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use `async/await`; avoid raw `Promise` chains
- Keep services thin; move complex logic to helpers or domain services
